
Link: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.2/topics/install/

If pip not found : sudo apt install python3-pip

Install venv (Virtual environnement for Python) :
sudo apt-get install python3-venv

Create a virtual environnement :
python3 -m venv env
(Check if a folder nammed 'env' appear)

Launch virtual environnement :
source env/bin/activate

Install django in venv :
python -m pip install Django

Install psycopg2 :
pip install psycopg2-binary

Go in JobBoard folder then, check if the back-end works :
python manage.py runserver 127.0.0.1:8000

Exit the virtual environnement :
deactivate


To install Django REST framework :
pip install djangorestframework
pip install markdown       # Markdown support for the browsable API.
pip install django-filter  # Filtering support


